From edf002d7c4ff8b3bf487c8e67b12ed2476c7cf5f Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Ripan Deuri <rdeuri@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Wed, 25 Jun 2025 17:48:12 +0530
Subject: [PATCH 2/3] QSDK: DP: wifi: ath12k: Tx completion handling
 optimization

The following optimizations are done in Tx completion handling:
1. Added budget in NAPI handling to avoid RCU and backpressure issues

2. Currently Tx completion code is organized as below:
   /* Reap Logic */
   Loop 1 {
       Fetch descriptor from HW and copy data into software strctures
   }

   /* Processing Logic and Tx descriptor replenish */
   Loop 2 {
       Fetch software tx descriptor using cookie
       Process tx descriptor and skb
       Attach tx descriptor back to free list acquiring required descriptor lock
   }

   In this patch, Tx completion handler has been revamped as below:

    Introduction and usage of scratch pad buffer "tx_status_buf[ATH12K_HW_MAX_QUEUES]".
    This memory is used to copy data from HW Tx descriptor entry at the
    time of reap. The field sw_metadata of this buffer are filled with all the
    data required for processing.

   /* Reap Logic */
   Loop 1 {
       Fetch descriptor from HW and copy data into scratch pad buffer
   }

   /* SW Tx Descriptor Reset and Replenish */
   Acquire descriptor lock
   Loop 2 {
       Copy data from tx_desc into sw metadata
       Reset tx_desc fields
   }
   Attach tx descriptors back to free list
   Release lock

   /* Processing Logic */
   Loop 3 {
       Processing of skb attached to sw_metadata
   }

   With above change, the tx descriptor replenish happens in batched mode
   and those are replenished even before skb processing which significantly
   reduces the contention.

